      <h3 class="fw-bold text-secondary mt-4 ">1. Keep It Short and Sweet</h3>
      <p class="w-100 lead">When it comes to video ads, less is more—especially if you’re working with a limited budget. You don’t need a five-minute cinematic masterpiece to captivate your audience. In fact, shorter videos tend to perform better because people’s attention spans are, well, short. Aim for 15 to 30 seconds. Think of your ad as a quick elevator pitch—what’s the one message you want your audience to take away?<br/><br/>
        Focus on one strong call-to-action (CTA). Whether it’s “Visit Our Website,” “Shop Now,” or “Download the App,” make it clear and concise. Don’t overcomplicate things by cramming in too much information. Your goal is to pique curiosity and encourage your audience to take the next step. A well-designed, straightforward message can make all the difference.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <h3 class="fw-bold text-secondary mt-4">2. Use What You Have—Be Resourceful!</h3>
      <p class="w-100 lead">Creating professional-looking video ads doesn’t mean hiring a Hollywood production crew. You likely already have the tools you need to get started. Your smartphone, for example, can shoot high-quality videos. Pair that with natural lighting, and you’ve got a recipe for success.<br/><br/>
        When it comes to advertising design, use free or affordable tools to enhance your videos. Apps like Canva or CapCut let you add text, transitions, and even animations without needing advanced editing skills. Repurpose content you’ve already created—turn testimonials, behind-the-scenes clips, or even product photos into engaging video slideshows. A little creativity goes a long way!<br/><br/>
        Feeling stuck? Use stock footage. Platforms like Pexels and Unsplash offer free video clips that can serve as the backdrop for your message. Add a voiceover or text overlay, and you’ve got a polished ad ready to go.
        </p>
    </div>
    </div>
    </div>
