          <div class="col">
            <h3 class="fw-bold text-secondary mt-4">3. Prioritize Storytelling Over Flashiness</h3>
            <p class="w-100 lead">Your video ad doesn’t need fancy effects or a massive budget to connect with your audience. What truly matters is the story you’re telling. Think about what makes your brand unique and how you can convey that in a relatable way.<br/><br/>
              For instance, if you’re a small bakery, showcase the process of making your signature pastry, from dough to deliciousness. Add a friendly voiceover explaining why your baked goods are the best in town. Authenticity beats perfection every time. People love ads that feel genuine and personal.<br/><br/>
              Don’t forget to focus on emotions. Whether it’s humor, nostalgia, or excitement, a well-crafted story evokes feelings that help your audience connect with your brand. Pairing your storytelling with clean, intentional advertising design ensures your message is both impactful and visually appealing.          
              </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3 class="fw-bold text-secondary mt-4">4. Optimize for Mobile Viewers</h3>
        <p class="w-100 lead">Most people will watch your video ads on their phones, so it’s crucial to design them with mobile users in mind. Vertical or square formats work best on platforms like Instagram, TikTok, and Facebook. These formats take up more screen space, making your ad stand out in a crowded feed.<br/><br/>
          Keep your visuals bold and simple, and make sure your text is large enough to read on a small screen. Since many people watch videos without sound, include captions or on-screen text to ensure your message gets across. Small tweaks like these can have a big impact on the effectiveness of your ads.          
          </p>
      </div>
      </div> 
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3 class="fw-bold text-secondary mt-4">5. Test, Tweak, and Try Again</h3>
        <p class="w-100 lead">The beauty of digital advertising design is that you can test and tweak your video ads in real time. Launch a few variations of your ad with different headlines, CTAs, or visuals, and see which performs best. Platforms like Facebook Ads Manager or Google Ads provide insights into metrics like engagement, clicks, and views.<br/><br/>
          Once you know what’s working, double down on those elements. If an ad with a bold, text-heavy design is performing better than one with a lot of visuals, use that insight for future campaigns. Testing doesn’t just save you money—it helps you get better results from every dollar spent.          
          </p>
      </div>
    </div>
